column1: Proportion of adults who do any walking or cycling, for any purpose, by frequency and local authority, England, 2018-2019
The figures in this table are outside the scope of National Statistics
"Walking" in this table refers to any continuous walk of over 10 minutes, irrespective of purpose.
"Cycling" in this table refers to any cycling, irrespective of length or purpose.
These statistics cover the time period mid-November 2018 to mid-November 2019.
Results are grouped according to the area where respondents live, which may not be the same as the area where they walk or cycle.
Sample sizes for the Isles of Scilly and City of London are very small and caution is needed in interpreting these results.
Source: Active Lives Survey - Sport England
